{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The easiest way to use Lighter is to use the “Enlighter” build tool plugin"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which is automatically run by Swift Package Manager or Xcode (14+) if the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"database files change."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"But if that isn’t an option (e.g. Xcode 14 can’t be used yet), Lighter"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"provides a set of options to do it otherwise."}]},{"anchor":"Using-the-Generate-Code-for-SQLite-command-plugin","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Using the “Generate Code for SQLite” command plugin."},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Command plugins are new Swift 5.6 feature that allows running commands embedded"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in packages manually (vs automatically as with “build tool plugins” like"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Enlighter)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"“Generate Code for SQLite” is a command plugin which looks at the database\/SQL"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"files just like Enlighter and produces Swift files for them. Unlike Enlighter"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it doesn’t write them into the build path, but into the sources of the project"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or package (SPM\/Xcode is prompting to allow for that)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In Xcode 14 the plugin can be run from the “File \/ Packages \/ Plugin” menu."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Note that Xcode 14 is only needed at generation time for that. Afterwards the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"file can be checked into the repository as source code."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Even with Xcode 13 the command plugin can be run using swift on the commandline."}]},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unless working on packages, Xcode doesn’t automatically add the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"generate Swift file."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"So on first run, one may need to look into the filesystem and drag the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"generated file into the project."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"anchor":"Using-the-Code-for-SQLite3-Application","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Using the “Code for SQLite3” Application"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/apps.apple.com\/us\/app\/code-for-sqlite3\/id1638111010"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is a macOS app that does the same like the “"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"swift2sqlite3"},{"type":"text","text":"” tool, but as an app."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It can be useful to play w\/ the Lighter options and to manually generate the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"code."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Just drag the database files into the app, and it’ll generate the Swift code."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Which can then be copy\/pasted into the Xcode project."}]},{"anchor":"Using-the-sqlite2swift-tool-manually","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Using the `sqlite2swift` tool manually"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is a useful option if Swift 5.6 is not yet available in a CI environment,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"but the code should be automatically generated. The tool can be added as a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"traditional script phase to a project."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The arguments:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1st argument:    The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lighter\/documentation\/Lighter\/Configuration"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-"},{"type":"text","text":" if there is none."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"2nd argument:    The name of the target the code is generated for, this is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"used to resolve configuration options in the file."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"other arguments: The database\/SQL input files."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"last argument:   The Swift output file."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sqlite2swift"},{"type":"text","text":" is shipped as a tool product in the Lighter package, and should"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"compile with Swift 5.0 and beyond."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/lighter\/manual"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Lighter\/documentation\/Lighter\/Manual","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"How to generate Lighter content by hand."}],"kind":"article","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Manual Generation","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"Lighter.swift for SQLite3"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Lighter\/documentation\/Lighter"]]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Advanced","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Lighter\/documentation\/Lighter\/Configuration","doc:\/\/Lighter\/documentation\/Lighter\/Linux","doc:\/\/Lighter\/documentation\/Lighter\/SQLiteAPI","doc:\/\/Lighter\/documentation\/Lighter\/Mapping","doc:\/\/Lighter\/documentation\/Lighter\/Performance"],"generated":true}],"references":{"doc://Lighter/documentation/Lighter/Configuration":{"role":"article","title":"Configuration","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Lighter.json"},{"type":"text","text":" configuration file."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lighter\/documentation\/Lighter\/Configuration","kind":"article","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/lighter\/configuration"},"doc://Lighter/documentation/Lighter/Linux":{"role":"article","title":"Linux","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Using Lighter on Linux."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lighter\/documentation\/Lighter\/Linux","kind":"article","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/lighter\/linux"},"doc://Lighter/documentation/Lighter":{"role":"collection","title":"Lighter.swift for SQLite3","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Type-safe down to the schema. Very, "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"very"}]},{"type":"text","text":", fast. Dependency free."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lighter\/documentation\/Lighter","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/lighter"},"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/code-for-sqlite3/id1638111010":{"title":"“Code for SQLite3” application","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"“Code for SQLite3” application"}],"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/apps.apple.com\/us\/app\/code-for-sqlite3\/id1638111010","url":"https:\/\/apps.apple.com\/us\/app\/code-for-sqlite3\/id1638111010"},"doc://Lighter/documentation/Lighter/SQLiteAPI":{"role":"article","title":"Dependency-Free API","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Using the dependency-free SQLite API."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lighter\/documentation\/Lighter\/SQLiteAPI","kind":"article","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/lighter\/sqliteapi"},"doc://Lighter/documentation/Lighter/Mapping":{"role":"collectionGroup","title":"Mapping","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Mapping Data retrieved from the Database."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lighter\/documentation\/Lighter\/Mapping","kind":"article","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/lighter\/mapping"},"doc://Lighter/documentation/Lighter/Performance":{"role":"article","title":"Performance","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A quick look at Lighter performance."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lighter\/documentation\/Lighter\/Performance","kind":"article","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/lighter\/performance"}}}